Canadian stocks fell for the first
time in seven days after the World Bank cut its global growth
forecast.  CML Healthcare Inc. (CLC)  slid 2.8 percent for the biggest drop
in the Standard & Poorâ€™s/TSX Composite Index after the company
said it will sell its diagnostic imaging business. Labrador Iron
Ore Royalty Corp. and Capstone Mining Corp. led declines in the
